      "side": 1,
      "message": "PTAL. I put ReadOnlyTransaction into the context too and removed all `txn` arguments everywhere.\n\nI\u0027m on the fence about this... On one hand it is (arguably) easier to read and write, no need to pass `txn` everywhere explicitly. On another: it is now not clear if a function needs a transaction, and of what kind. It is revealed only at runtime (it would panic if the context is not transactional).",
      "revId": "9cf8dce9c5ea34498dc338ef7f334b92974490da",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
